'''''The Goonies''''' is a 1986 [[platform game]] by [[Konami]] for the [[MSX]] based on the [[The Goonies|film of the same name]]. The music is a simple rendition of the song "[[The Goonies 'R' Good Enough]]", by [[Cyndi Lauper]].

==Development==
The game is based on the Famicom version with different levels.<ref name="GooniesG">{{cite web | url=http://www.hardcoregaming101.net/goonies-the-konami/ | title=Goonies, the (Konami) – Hardcore Gaming 101}}</ref>

In 2006, an independent dev team named Bran Games remade the game for Windows as freeware. The remake has improved graphics, visual and sound effects.<ref name="GooniesG"/>

==Gameplay==
''The Goonies'' is a platform and puzzle game, featuring five 'scenes'. After each successfully completed scene, a key word is given and thus the player can continue the game from this point at any time.

